reviews.review_text:
One of My Favorite Shows of All Time I can't believe nobody has written a review of this show. 

I managed to hit exactly 75 shows between 1982 and 1995, with highlights including western tour, fall 1983 and 4 NYE shows among others. This was one of my favorites. My best friend worked for GDTS in the 90's but I only saw about 10 shows during the entire 1990's. Wish I took advantange of the passes more than I did. I was backstage at the last 2 shows at Soldier Field where a very pastey Jerry walked right past me on his way to the stage. 

This show was my 3rd NY run and I was in an especially "happy" mood this night.  It was only a 2-show run, so this was the first. 

I was getting pretty well connected in the Dead scene by this point so we had heard about them rehearsing Mighty Quinn and were expecting it at one of these 2 shows. 

The first set of this show is very strong, except Looks Like Rain,  which I can always do without.  Bobby was playing a new guitar which sounded really spooky, especially with the state I was in.  I love the sound of that guitar in this show.

Not much to say about the second set,  except look at the setlist. Mighty Quinn blew everyone away. 

I had a cassette copy of this show the next day. It was my only copy until I got a DAT copy of the cassette SBD of it in 1997. I think this recording is the same as my DAT copy.  It's better than the audience cassette I had but not as nice as some other boards.

I hope people find this show and add some comments here.  It certainly seems to be one of those nuggets that go unnoticed.  Glad I could provide some feedback.

This a Good-un All good -- both sets. Standouts: Mighty Quinn, Crazy Fingers, Other One, Wharf Rat.

There is an AUD patch (?) during the last verse of Fingers and it renders the vocal tender and delicate, yet it completely consumes every square inch of that arena and drenches it with an indescribably breathy texture. Truly amazing piece of work. Astounding.
12-30-85 Very good. A nice sounding remaster by Charlie too.

Great '85 Show still after all these years - this show delivers.  i love the echo on LL Rain and the Sugar is one of my all time favs.  I believe this is the Sugar Mags where Bobby climbing on the speakers and Phil and Gracia straight into SSDD (as related in Phil's book)...turn it up - this is for cranking
We Are Everywhere Wow, what a way to end a year of fun and frolic! What a great group of folks I had the pleasure to hang-out with! Show was stellar. God Bless Mark O! Oh the Reagan years.
My first show I remember it as if it were yesterday. I was 15. My anticipation was thick, and they didn't disappoint. If I could only go back...

18 years young With no tickets or money my friends and I loaded up the car drove from Salt Lake City to Oakland. I had no idea that this, my first show, would forever change the way I viewed the world. Truly a life changing experience.

If i had my way~!!!!! Crisp clean SBD..Love this show..Quintessential 85' Dead~
The Mighty Quinn>Samson is off the hook~!! Jerry shreds the Samson and his voice sounds haunting>Give It A Whirl>Forever Grateful>Forever Dead
